2 Home.
3 § 1752. DEFINITIONS
4 As used in this chapter:
5 (1) “Compensation” means payment of money, a thing of value, or a
6 financial benefit.
7 (2) “Veterans’ benefits matter” means the preparation, presentation, or
8 prosecution of a claim affecting an individual who has filed or expressed an
9 intent to file a claim for a benefit, program, service, commodity, function, or
10 status, entitlement to which is determined under the laws and regulations
11 administered by the U.S. Department of Veterans Affairs or the U.S.
12 Department of Defense pertaining to veterans, their dependents, their
13 survivors, and any other individual eligible for such benefits.
14 § 1753. PROHIBITED CONDUCT
15 (a) For purposes of this section, “person” does not include an accredited
16 representative of a recognized organization or an accredited agent or attorney
17 pursuant to 38 C.F.R. § 14.629 (requirements for accreditation), as amended,
18 or individuals working within their capacity as employees of the Vermont
19 Office of Veterans Affairs or the Vermont Veterans’ Home.
20 (b) The following conduct is prohibited:
