1 (1) No person shall receive compensation for advising any individual
2 with regard to any veterans’ benefits matter, except as permitted under Title 38
3 of the United States Code and the regulations adopted pursuant to Title 38, as
4 amended.
5 (2) No person shall receive compensation for referring any individual to
6 another person for advice, consultation, or assistance with regard to any
7 veterans’ benefits matter.
8 (3) No person shall receive compensation for any services rendered
9 before the date on which a notice of disagreement, decision review, or appeal
10 is filed, whichever occurs first, with respect to an individual’s veterans’
11 benefits matter.
12 (4) No person shall guarantee, either directly or by implication, that any
13 individual is certain to receive specific veterans’ benefits or that any individual
14 is certain to receive a specific level, percentage, or amount of veterans’
15 benefits.
16 (5) No person offering advice, consultation, or assistance with regard to
17 any veterans’ benefits matter shall falsely claim or represent, either directly or
18 indirectly, that the person is sponsored by, affiliated with, or accredited by the
19 U.S. Department of Veterans Affairs, the Vermont Office of Veterans Affairs,
20 or the Vermont Veterans’ Home.
21 § 1754. MEMORIALIZATION OF TERMS
