1 A person seeking to receive compensation for advising, consulting, or
2 assisting an individual with a veterans’ benefits matter shall, before rendering
3 any services, memorialize all terms regarding payment for services to be
4 rendered in a written agreement, signed by both parties. To be valid, the
5 written agreement must adhere to all criteria specified in 38 C.F.R. § 14.636(g)
6 (fee agreements), as amended.
7 § 1755. FEES
8 No person shall receive excessive or unreasonable fees as compensation for
9 advising or assisting an individual with any veterans’ benefits matter. Factors
10 to be considered in determining whether fees are excessive or unreasonable
11 include those specified in 38 C.F.R. § 14.636(e) (fee reasonableness factors),
12 as amended.
13 § 1756. VIOLATION
14 (a) A violation of this chapter is deemed to be a violation of 9 V.S.A.
15 § 2453.
16 (b) The Attorney General or a State’s Attorney has the same authority to
17 make rules, conduct civil investigations, enter into assurances of
18 discontinuance, and bring civil actions, and private parties have the same rights
19 and remedies, as provided under 9 V.S.A. chapter 63, subchapter 1.
20 Sec. 2. EFFECTIVE DATE
21 This act shall take effect on July 1, 2025.
